-- Xing Lin Medical to Raise Up to HK$41.2 Million in Placing, Make Purchase
-- B y   J o s h u a   F e l l m a n
-- 2010-09-24T15:07:03Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-09-24/xing-lin-medical-to-raise-up-to-hk-41-2-million-in-placing-make-purchase.html
Xing Lin Medical Information
Technology Co.  said it will raise as much as HK$41.2 million to
repay a promissory note through a placing of 227.8 million
shares at 18.1 Hong Kong cents each.  Kingston Securities Ltd. will act as placing agent for the
placement, receiving a 1 percent commission for the “best
effort” sale to at least six independent investors, Xing Lin
said in a Hong Kong stock-exchange statement today.  Separately, Xing Lin also said it will buy a company that
is developing a regional health-care information collaboration
system in Liuzhou, China for HK$45 million.  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Joshua Fellman at 
 jfellman@bloomberg.net  